# Mobile UX Constraints & Solutions

This document addresses the unique challenges of fitting a complex American Mahjong game onto small mobile screens, with performance considerations, touch interactions, and information density solutions.

---

## 1. Screen Size Constraints

### 1.1 Target Devices & Breakpoints

 | Device Class | Resolution | Screen Size | Orientation | Design Priority |
 | -------------- | ----------- | ------------- | ------------- | ---------------- |
 | **Small Phone** | 375×667 (iPhone SE) | 4.7" | Portrait | Primary target |
 | **Medium Phone** | 390×844 (iPhone 12) | 6.1" | Portrait | Primary target |
 | **Large Phone** | 414×896 (iPhone 11 Pro Max) | 6.5" | Portrait & Landscape | Secondary |
 | **Tablet** | 768×1024 (iPad Mini) | 7.9" | Portrait & Landscape | Tertiary |

**Design Philosophy**: Mobile-first, progressive enhancement.

**Critical Constraint**: Must fit all essential game information within 375px width (iPhone SE) without horizontal scrolling.

---

### 1.2 Information Hierarchy on Small Screens

**Challenge**: Desktop UI shows simultaneously:

- Your hand (13+ tiles)

- 3 opponents' areas

- Discard pile

- The Card viewer

- Action buttons

- Timers, scores, turn indicator

**Mobile Reality**: 375×667px = ~250,000px² total area. Can't fit everything.

**Solution - Layered Information Architecture**:

#### Layer 1: Always Visible (Top 1/3)

- **Header Bar (60px height)**:

  - Current phase indicator

  - Whose turn (mini indicator)

  - Timer (circular, 40px)

  - Menu button (hamburger)

**Total:** 60px used, 607px remaining

#### Layer 2: Contextual Middle (Middle 1/3)

- **Opponent Summary (200px height)**:

  - Compact 3-player layout (stacked vertically or semi-circle)

  - Concealed tile count only (no visible tiles)

  - Active turn indicator

  - Exposed melds (horizontal scroll if needed)

**Total:** 260px used, 407px remaining

#### Layer 3: Player Hand (Bottom 1/3)

- **Your Hand (280px height)**:

  - Horizontal scrollable tile rack

  - 5-6 tiles visible at once (swipe to see more)

  - Action buttons below hand

**Remaining:** 127px for action bar

#### Layer 4: Overlays (Modals)

- **The Card**: Full-screen modal (triggered by button)

- **Discard Pile**: Bottom sheet modal (swipe up)

- **Call Window**: Full-screen takeover

- **Settings**: Slide-in drawer

---

### 1.3 Visual Space Budget (375×667px Portrait)

 | Element | Height | Justification |
 | --------- | -------- | --------------- |
 | Status bar (iOS) | 44px | System UI (can't control) |
 | Header bar | 60px | Phase, turn, timer, menu |
 | Opponent areas | 200px | 3 opponents stacked |
 | Discard pile preview | 0px | Hidden by default (modal-only) |
 | Your hand | 280px | 5 tiles visible + scroll |
 | Action buttons | 60px | 1 row, 2-3 buttons max |
 | Safe area (iOS) | 23px | Bottom home indicator |
 | **Total** | **667px** | Exact fit ✅ |

**Key Trade-off**: Discard pile is hidden by default. Access via:

- Tap center of screen → Opens discard pile modal

- Or swipe up from bottom → Bottom sheet

---

## 2. Touch Interaction Constraints

### 2.1 Minimum Touch Target Sizes

**iOS Human Interface Guidelines**: 44×44pt minimum.

**Android Material Design**: 48×48dp minimum.

**Our Standard**: **48×48px minimum** (compromise, works on both).

**Problem**: Tiles on mobile are 48×64px. 13 tiles at 48px width + 4px gap = 676px total width.

**Reality**: Screen is only 375px wide.

**Solution**: Horizontal scroll (only 5-6 tiles visible at once).

---

### 2.2 Thumb Zones (One-Handed Use)

**Research**: 49% of users hold phone in one hand (Hoober, 2013).

**Thumb Reach Map (Right Hand)**:

```text
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│ 🔴 Hard to Reach (Top Corners)  │ (Error rate: 20%)
│                                 │
│ 🟡 Awkward (Top Center)         │ (Error rate: 10%)
│                                 │
│ 🟢 Easy (Center)                │ (Error rate: 3%)
│                                 │
│ 🟢 Natural (Bottom Third)       │ (Error rate: 1%)
└─────────────────────────────────┘

```

text

text

text

text

**Design Rule**: Place primary actions in bottom 1/3 of screen.

**Application**:

- ✅ **Good**: Action buttons at bottom (Discard, Call, Pass)

- ❌ **Bad**: Menu button in top-left corner

- ✅ **Fix**: Move menu to top-right OR bottom-left corner

---

### 2.3 Touch Accuracy & Error Prevention

**Challenge**: Adjacent tiles are only 4px apart. Accidental taps are common.

**Solutions**:

#### Solution A: Increased Touch Padding (Invisible)

```css
.tile {
  width: 48px;
  height: 64px;
  /* Visual size */
}

.tile::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  inset: -8px; /* Expand touch target to 64×80px */
  z-index: -1;
}

```

text

text

text

text

**Trade-off**: Tiles now overlap in touch space. Need intelligent hit detection.

#### Solution B: Tap Confirmation (Charleston)

- **First tap**: Tile lifts up (selected state)

- **Second tap**: Deselect

- **Long press**: Show details

- **No accidental actions** (require "Confirm Pass" button)

#### Solution C: Undo Button

- After discarding, show "Undo" toast for 2 seconds

- Allows quick recovery from mis-taps

- Only in practice mode (not competitive)

---

### 2.4 Gesture Conflicts

**Problem**: Horizontal swipe to scroll hand vs. vertical swipe to open discard pile.

**Solution - Clear Gesture Zones**:

```text
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│ Vertical swipe: Open menu      │ (Top 60px)
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│ Tap: View opponent details     │ (Opponents area)
│                                 │
│ Vertical swipe: Discard pile   │ (Center)
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│ Horizontal swipe: Scroll hand  │ (Hand area only)
│                                 │
│ Tap: Action buttons            │ (Bottom buttons)
└─────────────────────────────────┘

```

text

text

text

text

**Implementation**:

- Detect swipe direction in first 50ms

- Lock to axis (horizontal OR vertical, not both)

- Prevent diagonal swipes

---

## 3. Information Density Solutions

### 3.1 The Card Viewer on Mobile

**Challenge**: Desktop Card viewer shows 6 patterns simultaneously. Mobile can fit 1-2.

**Solution - Progressive Disclosure**:

#### Mobile Card Viewer Layout

```text
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│ 2025 Card          [Close ×]    │
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│ Filter: [All ▼]  [Search 🔍]    │
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│                                 │
│ ⭐ 2468 Consecutive (25 pts)    │ <- Highlighted (matches hand)
│ 2222 4444 6666 88               │
│ [View Details →]                │
│                                 │
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│                                 │
│ Winds & Dragons (30 pts)        │
│ EEEE SSSS WWWW NN               │
│ [View Details →]                │
│                                 │
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│ (Scroll for 48 more patterns)   │
└─────────────────────────────────┘

```

text

text

text

text

**Features**:

- **Highlight matches**: Patterns matching your hand appear at top with ⭐

- **Collapse by default**: Show 2-line preview, tap to expand

- **Sticky filter**: Filter bar stays at top during scroll

- **Search**: Type "wind" to filter to wind patterns

---

