## 4. Performance Constraints

### 4.1 Mobile Hardware Limitations

 | Device | CPU | RAM | GPU | Target FPS |
 | -------- | ----- | ----- | ----- | ----------- |
 | iPhone SE (2020) | A13 Bionic | 3GB | 4-core GPU | 60fps |
 | Android Budget (Snapdragon 660) | Octa-core | 4GB | Adreno 512 | 30fps |

**Design Constraint**: Must run smoothly on 3-year-old budget Android devices.

**Implications**:

- Limit simultaneous animations (max 3 tiles animating at once)

- Use CSS transforms only (GPU-accelerated)

- Avoid large images (use SVG tiles when possible)

- Lazy load The Card data (don't parse all 50 patterns upfront)

---

### 4.2 Network Performance (Mobile Data)

**Scenario**: User on 3G connection (latency: 100-500ms, bandwidth: 1 Mbps).

**Impact on UX**:

- WebSocket events delayed by 100-500ms

- Large messages (e.g., game state snapshot) take 2-3 seconds

**Solutions**:

#### Optimistic UI

```javascript
// User taps "Discard"
discardTile(tile) {
  // Immediate: Show tile animating to discard pile (optimistic)
  animateTileToDiscardPile(tile);

  // Send command to server (may take 200ms)
  sendCommand({ type: 'Discard', tile });

  // If server rejects (rare), roll back animation
  socket.on('Error', () => {
    rollbackAnimation(tile);
    showError('Discard rejected by server');
  });
}

```

text

text

text

text

**Perceived latency**: 0ms (instant feedback), actual latency: 200ms (server confirms).

#### Message Compression

- Use binary encoding (Protobuf or MessagePack) instead of JSON

- Reduce WebSocket message size by 60%

- Example: `{"type":"Discard","tile":{"suit":"Bam","rank":3}}` (45 bytes) → `[2,0,3]` (3 bytes)

---

### 4.3 Battery Performance

**Challenge**: Continuous WebSocket connection + animations drain battery.

**Measurement**: Typical game session (20 minutes) should consume < 5% battery.

**Solutions**:

#### Reduce Animation Frame Rate

```javascript
// Desktop: 60fps animations
// Mobile (low battery): 30fps animations

if (isMobile && batteryLevel < 0.2) {
  disableAnimations(); // Skip tile animations, instant transitions
}

```

text

text

text

text

#### Throttle Heartbeats

```javascript
// Desktop: Heartbeat every 5s
// Mobile (backgrounded): Heartbeat every 30s
// Mobile (foregrounded): Heartbeat every 10s

if (document.hidden) {
  setHeartbeatInterval(30000); // 30s
} else {
  setHeartbeatInterval(10000); // 10s
}

```

text

text

text

text

#### Suspend Non-Essential Features

- Background blur effects: Disable on mobile

- Particle effects (confetti on win): Simplify or disable

- Shadows on tiles: Reduce blur radius

---

### 4.4 Memory Constraints

**Challenge**: Mobile browsers limit JavaScript heap to 512MB-1GB. Avoid memory leaks.

**Common Leaks in React**:

- Unused event listeners

- Uncancelled timers

- Retained DOM references

**Solution - Cleanup Pattern**:

```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  const timer = setInterval(() => {
    updateTurnTimer();
  }, 1000);

  return () => clearInterval(timer); // ✅ Cleanup on unmount
}, []);

```

text

text

text

text

**Memory Budget**:

- Tile assets: < 2MB total (13 tiles × 42 types × 4KB each)

- Game state: < 100KB

- React components: < 10MB

- Total: < 50MB for entire app

**Monitoring**: Use Chrome DevTools Memory profiler, check for heap growth over time.

---

## 5. Orientation & Layout Shifts

### 5.1 Portrait vs. Landscape Layouts

**Portrait (Primary)**:

- Vertical stack: Header → Opponents → Hand → Actions

- 375px wide: Fits 5 tiles at 48px each

**Landscape (Secondary)**:

- Horizontal layout: Opponents on sides, hand at bottom

- 667px wide: Fits 11 tiles (nearly full hand visible)

**Challenge**: User rotates mid-game. Layout must adapt instantly.

**Solution - Responsive Grid**:

```css
.game-container {
  display: grid;
}

/* Portrait */
@media (orientation: portrait) {
  .game-container {
    grid-template-rows: 60px 200px 1fr 60px;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}

/* Landscape */
@media (orientation: landscape) {
  .game-container {
    grid-template-rows: 60px 1fr 80px;
    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr 200px;
  }
}

```

text

text

text

text

**Transition**: Crossfade (200ms) during rotation to prevent jarring relayout.

---

### 5.2 Safe Area Insets (Notch & Home Indicator)

**Challenge**: iPhone X+ has notch (top) and home indicator (bottom). Content can be obscured.

**Solution - CSS Safe Areas**:

```css
.header {
  padding-top: env(safe-area-inset-top); /* Avoid notch */
}

.action-bar {
  padding-bottom: env(safe-area-inset-bottom); /* Avoid home indicator */
}

```

text

text

text

text

**Viewport Meta Tag**:

```html
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, viewport-fit=cover">

```

text

text

text

text

**Result**: App expands to full screen, avoids notch/indicator.

---

## 6. Offline & Low-Connectivity UX

### 6.1 Offline Detection

**Scenario**: User's internet cuts out mid-game.

**Detection**:

```javascript
window.addEventListener('offline', () => {
  showReconnectingModal();
});

window.addEventListener('online', () => {
  attemptReconnect();
});

```

text

text

text

text

**UX Response**:

```text
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│ 📡 No Internet                  │
├─────────────────────────────────┤
│ You are offline. Game paused.   │
│                                 │
│ Your game will be saved for 60s.│
│                                 │
│ [Retry Connection]              │
└─────────────────────────────────┘

```

text

text

text

text

---

### 6.2 Slow Connection Indicators

**Scenario**: User on slow 2G connection. Everything lags.

**Detection**: Measure WebSocket round-trip time (RTT).

```javascript
const ping = Date.now();
socket.send('ping');

socket.on('pong', () => {
  const rtt = Date.now() - ping;

  if (rtt > 500) {
    showSlowConnectionWarning();
  }
});

```

text

text

text

text

**UX Response**:

```text
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│ 🐌 Slow Connection              │
│ Latency: 650ms                  │
│                                 │
│ Game may be sluggish.           │
│ [Switch to WiFi?]               │
└─────────────────────────────────┘

```

text

text

text

text

