## 9. Accessibility on Mobile

### 9.1 VoiceOver (iOS) Navigation

**Challenge**: Swipe navigation on iOS conflicts with horizontal tile scrolling.

**Solution - VoiceOver Rotor**:

- Enable "Containers" rotor option

- Tiles are grouped: "Your Hand, 13 tiles"

- Swipe right to navigate between tiles

- Double-tap to select

**Implementation**:

```html
<div role="list" aria-label="Your hand, 13 tiles">
  <div role="listitem" aria-label="1 Bamboo, not selected">
    <button aria-pressed="false">1B</button>
  </div>
  <!-- ... 12 more tiles ... -->
</div>

```

text

text

text

text

---

### 9.2 TalkBack (Android) Navigation

**Challenge**: TalkBack reads tiles left-to-right, but user may have scrolled.

**Solution - Focus Management**:

```javascript
// When user scrolls, announce current visible range
scrollContainer.addEventListener('scroll', debounce(() => {
  const firstVisibleTile = getFirstVisibleTile();
  announce(`Showing tiles ${firstVisibleTile} to ${firstVisibleTile + 5}`);
}, 300));

```

text

text

text

text

---

### 9.3 Zoom & Text Scaling

**iOS Setting**: Settings → Display → Text Size (up to 200%).

**Challenge**: User increases text size to 200%. Layout breaks.

**Solution - Responsive Typography**:

```css
/* Use rem units (scales with user preference) */
.tile-rank {
  font-size: 1.5rem; /* Scales with text size setting */
}

/* Prevent layout overflow */
.hand-container {
  overflow-x: auto; /* Horizontal scroll if tiles too wide */
}

```

text

text

text

text

**Testing**: Use iOS Accessibility Inspector, test at 200% text size.

---

## 10. Mobile-Specific Edge Cases

### 10.1 Tap During Animation

**Scenario**: User taps a tile while it's animating (e.g., Charleston pass).

**Problem**: Tap registers on wrong tile (tile moved during animation).

**Solution - Disable Interaction During Animation**:

```javascript
function animateTile(tile) {
  tile.classList.add('animating');
  tile.style.pointerEvents = 'none'; // Disable taps

  setTimeout(() => {
    tile.classList.remove('animating');
    tile.style.pointerEvents = 'auto'; // Re-enable taps
  }, 500);
}

```

text

text

text

text

---

### 10.2 Accidental Swipe-Back (iOS Safari)

**Scenario**: User swipes from left edge to go back (browser navigation).

**Problem**: Triggers browser "back" button, leaves game.

**Solution - Prevent Edge Swipe**:

```javascript
// Detect swipe from left edge (< 20px)
document.addEventListener('touchstart', (e) => {
  if (e.touches[0].clientX < 20) {
    e.preventDefault(); // Prevent back navigation
  }
});

```

text

text

text

text

---

### 10.3 Haptic Feedback (Optional Enhancement)

**Feature**: Vibrate on tile selection, discard, call.

**Implementation**:

```javascript
function selectTile(tile) {
  // Visual feedback
  tile.classList.add('selected');

  // Haptic feedback (if supported)
  if (navigator.vibrate) {
    navigator.vibrate(10); // 10ms buzz
  }
}

```

text

text

text

text

**User Preference**: Add toggle in settings (some users dislike vibrations).

---

## 11. Mobile Performance Checklist

Before shipping mobile UI:

- [ ] Test on iPhone SE (375×667, smallest screen)

- [ ] Test on budget Android (Snapdragon 660, 4GB RAM)

- [ ] Test on 3G connection (throttle network in DevTools)

- [ ] Test with 6x CPU slowdown (DevTools Performance tab)

- [ ] Test in landscape orientation

- [ ] Test with VoiceOver/TalkBack enabled

- [ ] Test at 200% text size

- [ ] Test with low battery mode enabled

- [ ] Measure battery drain (< 5% per 20min session)

- [ ] Measure memory usage (< 50MB total)

- [ ] Measure bundle size (< 150KB gzipped)

- [ ] Test offline mode (airplane mode)

- [ ] Test reconnection after 60s disconnect

- [ ] Test background/foreground transitions

- [ ] Test with slow animations disabled (accessibility setting)

---

## 12. Mobile-Specific Metrics

 | Metric | Target | Measurement Method |
 | -------- | -------- | -------------------- |
 | First Contentful Paint | < 1.5s | Lighthouse (throttled 3G) |
 | Time to Interactive | < 3s | Lighthouse |
 | Tile Tap Response | < 100ms | Custom performance mark |
 | Scroll FPS | 60fps | Chrome DevTools FPS meter |
 | Bundle Size | < 150KB gzipped | Webpack bundle analyzer |
 | Memory Usage | < 50MB | Chrome DevTools Memory profiler |
 | Battery Drain | < 5% per 20min | Manual testing (Settings → Battery) |
 | Touch Target Size | ≥ 48×48px | Manual measurement (DevTools) |

